"use strict";(self.webpackChunkwebsite_new=self.webpackChunkwebsite_new||[]).push([[6114],{58502(e){e.exports=JSON.parse('{"archive":{"blogPosts":[{"id":"rayforge-1.6-device-profiles-rotary-print-cut","metadata":{"permalink":"/fr/blog/rayforge-1.6-device-profiles-rotary-print-cut","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-24-rayforge-1.6-device-profiles-rotary-print-cut.md","title":"Rayforge 1.6 - Device Profiles, Rotary Overhaul, Print & Cut","description":"Rayforge 1.6 brings a complete rotary overhaul, device profiles, a redesigned layer system, per-layer WCS, and a Print and Cut addon.","date":"2026-04-24T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"1.6","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/1-6"},{"inline":true,"label":"rotary","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/rotary"},{"inline":true,"label":"device-profiles","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/device-profiles"},{"inline":true,"label":"print-and-cut","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/print-and-cut"},{"inline":true,"label":"layers","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/layers"}],"readingTime":2.6,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Rayforge Team","title":"Core development team","url":"https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge","imageURL":"/fr/images/icon.svg","key":"rayforge_team","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"rayforge-1.6-device-profiles-rotary-print-cut","title":"Rayforge 1.6 - Device Profiles, Rotary Overhaul, Print & Cut","authors":"rayforge_team","tags":["release","1.6","rotary","device-profiles","print-and-cut","layers"],"description":"Rayforge 1.6 brings a complete rotary overhaul, device profiles, a redesigned layer system, per-layer WCS, and a Print and Cut addon."},"unlisted":false,"nextItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.5 - 3D Simulator, Bezier Curves, No-Go Zones","permalink":"/fr/blog/rayforge-1.5-3d-simulator-bezier-nogozones"}},"content":"Rayforge 1.6 brings a complete rotary axis overhaul, a new device profile\\nsystem, a redesigned layer system with per-layer WCS, and a Print and Cut addon\\nfor aligning laser cuts with printed material.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Device Profiles\\n\\nMachine profiles have been replaced by **device profiles** -- declarative\\npackages that bundle your work area, axis setup, laser settings, and G-code\\ndialect into a single file. Pick your device and everything is pre-configured.\\nYou can export and import profiles to share setups between machines or back up\\nyour configuration.\\n\\n## Rotary Axis Overhaul\\n\\nRotary support was rewritten from the ground up with proper kinematics. The new\\nsystem supports a **true 4th axis** alongside your existing X, Y, and Z axes,\\nas well as **axis replacement mode** for setups where the rotary takes over X\\nor Y. Roller-type rotary attachments get their own dedicated settings.\\n\\nThe 2D canvas adapts to rotary mode automatically, and the 3D canvas renders\\nrotary toolpaths correctly in every configuration -- including during simulation\\nplayback. The kinematics engine was refactored to build dynamically from an axis\\nset and mapper, making it far more flexible and correct.\\n\\n## Print and Cut\\n\\nA new addon helps you align laser cuts with pre-printed material. Register\\nreference points on your print, let Rayforge calculate the offset and rotation,\\nand your cuts land exactly where they should. Perfect for making stickers,\\nlabels, or anything that needs to line up with an existing print.\\n\\n## Redesigned Layer System\\n\\nThe layer panel got a complete overhaul. Each layer column now shows a visual\\nworkflow so you can see your operations at a glance. You can reorder layers and\\nworkpieces with drag-and-drop. Each layer can be assigned its own Work\\nCoordinate System (G54-G59) for multi-fixture setups, with a quick edit button\\nright in the layer settings. The settings dialog is non-modal, so you can keep\\nit open while working on the canvas.\\n\\n## Material Test Grid\\n\\nNew parameter combinations are available, and multipass mode now shows extra\\nspeed or power labels so you can tell exactly what each cell represents.\\n\\n## GRBL Telnet Driver\\n\\nCommunity contributor gyordanov built a new driver that connects to GRBL\\ncontrollers over the network via Telnet. It works with grblHAL and ESP3D-based\\nboards -- no USB cable needed.\\n\\n## Other Improvements\\n\\n- **Update checker** notifies you when a new version is available\\n- **Floating properties panel** gives you more canvas space\\n- **Editable slider values** -- click and type the exact number you want\\n- **Ops color setting** -- choose layer color or laser color for rendering\\n- **Creality Falcon A1** device profile\\n- **Massively reduced memory** usage for multi-layer PDFs\\n- **GRBL serial improvements** with deadlock recovery and comment stripping\\n- **Sketcher** -- support changing text color using the fill tool\\n- **Canvas** -- right-click context menu for empty space\\n- **Windows** -- terminal window no longer appears on startup\\n\\n## Special Thanks\\n\\nThis release was made possible with the support of our Patreon supporters:\\nold-man-and-the-seam, Amsel, froqstar, pghpete, Derek McTavish, and four\\nanonymous supporters.\\n\\n## Download Rayforge 1.6\\n\\n- [GitHub Releases](/docs/getting-started/installation)\\n- [Website](https://rayforge.org/)\\n\\n## Join the Community\\n\\n- [Discord](https://discord.gg/sTHNdTtpQJ)\\n- [Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/c/knipknap)"},{"id":"rayforge-1.5-3d-simulator-bezier-nogozones","metadata":{"permalink":"/fr/blog/rayforge-1.5-3d-simulator-bezier-nogozones","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-09-rayforge-1.5-3d-simulator-bezier-nogozones.md","title":"Rayforge 1.5 - 3D Simulator, Bezier Curves, No-Go Zones","description":"Rayforge 1.5 adds a full 3D job simulator with playback controls, native cubic bezier G5 support, no-go zones with collision checking, and major performance gains.","date":"2026-04-09T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"1.5","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/1-5"},{"inline":true,"label":"simulator","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/simulator"},{"inline":true,"label":"bezier","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/bezier"},{"inline":true,"label":"nogozones","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/nogozones"},{"inline":true,"label":"performance","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/performance"}],"readingTime":3.34,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Rayforge Team","title":"Core development team","url":"https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge","imageURL":"/fr/images/icon.svg","key":"rayforge_team","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"rayforge-1.5-3d-simulator-bezier-nogozones","title":"Rayforge 1.5 - 3D Simulator, Bezier Curves, No-Go Zones","authors":"rayforge_team","tags":["release","1.5","simulator","bezier","nogozones","performance"],"description":"Rayforge 1.5 adds a full 3D job simulator with playback controls, native cubic bezier G5 support, no-go zones with collision checking, and major performance gains."},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.6 - Device Profiles, Rotary Overhaul, Print & Cut","permalink":"/fr/blog/rayforge-1.6-device-profiles-rotary-print-cut"},"nextItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.4 - Rotary Axis, PDF Layers, Camera Calibration","permalink":"/fr/blog/rayforge-1.4-rotary-pdf-camera"}},"content":"Rayforge 1.5 adds a full 3D job simulator with playback controls, native\\ncubic bezier curve support (G5), no-go zones with collision checking, and\\nsignificant performance and memory improvements.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## 3D Simulator\\n\\nThe 3D canvas now has a complete job simulator. You can watch your job execute\\nstep by step -- the laser head moves along the toolpath, the beam appears when\\nthe laser fires, and bitmap engravings are progressively revealed as the\\nplayhead advances.\\n\\nPlayback controls sit at the bottom of the canvas: play/pause, step forward\\nand backward, a scrubber slider, and a speed button that cycles through 1x\\nto 16x. Rotary mode works too -- the cylinder rotates along with the\\nsimulation. All of this runs without blocking the rest of the interface, even\\non complex jobs.\\n\\n## Bezier Curves (G5)\\n\\nRayforge now supports native cubic bezier curves through the entire pipeline --\\nfrom import all the way to G-code output. For machines running LinuxCNC or\\nMarlin, curves are emitted as G5 commands instead of thousands of tiny line\\nsegments. The result is smoother cuts, smaller G-code files, and faster\\nexecution. For machines that don\'t support G5 (Grbl, Smoothieware, and\\nothers), curves are automatically linearized -- no configuration needed.\\n\\nThis touched nearly every part of the system. Tabs, cropping, smoothing,\\nmulti-pass, and path optimization all handle curves properly now.\\n\\n## No-Go Zones\\n\\nYou can now define restricted areas in your machine settings. These mark areas\\non the bed where the laser should not cut -- clamps, fixtures, or that corner\\nwhere the hose always gets in the way. Rayforge checks for collisions and warns\\nyou before sending G-code.\\n\\n## Performance and Memory\\n\\nThe canvas is significantly more responsive. When you drag, pan, or zoom,\\nexpensive laser-path rendering is suppressed until you stop moving -- no more\\nstuttering while repositioning a workpiece. Multi-step workflows render faster\\nbecause all visible steps are composited into a single surface.\\n\\nLarge images that used to cause multi-gigabyte memory spikes are now\\nautomatically scaled to sensible limits. The image handling was rewritten to\\navoid unnecessary copies, and caching is smarter -- shared images are rendered\\nonce and reused across workpieces. Two memory leaks in the 3D simulator were\\nalso fixed.\\n\\n## Dockable Bottom Panel\\n\\nThe bottom panel tabs can now be rearranged freely. Drag a tab onto the divider\\nbetween columns to split it off into its own column. You can keep the layer\\nlist and G-code viewer visible side by side, for example. The layout persists\\nbetween sessions.\\n\\n## Asset Browser\\n\\nThe asset browser has been overhauled. All assets are visible and can be\\ndragged to the canvas or to a specific layer. Multi-selection works for\\ndrag-and-drop and bulk deletion. Thumbnails are generated for most image\\nformats, and when the browser is empty it shows a helpful placeholder with\\nbuttons to add stock or a sketch.\\n\\n## New Import Options\\n\\nThe import dialog offers three layer modes: flatten into the current layer,\\ncreate new layers from the file, or map imported layers onto existing ones.\\nAfter import, Rayforge adds sensible default workflow steps -- a Contour step\\nfor vector layers and an Engrave step for layers with fills.\\n\\n## Lead-In / Lead-Out\\n\\nA new lead-in/lead-out postprocessor adds zero-power approach and exit moves\\nat the start and end of each contour. This helps the laser reach constant\\nvelocity before the actual cut begins, improving cut quality at entry and exit\\npoints.\\n\\n## Other Improvements\\n\\n- 3D model support for rotary axes (GLB format)\\n- Continuous laser mode and modal feedrate G-code options\\n- GRBL raster dialect with cleaner M4/M5 handling\\n- Grbl MKS DLC32 machine profile\\n- Material test: labels engraved first, overscan support, label speed setting\\n- Ctrl+F search in console and G-code viewer\\n- YUYV camera protocol support\\n- Addons can register toggles in the View menu\\n- Status bar removed, info moved to contextual locations\\n- Single instance lock\\n\\n## Download Rayforge 1.5\\n\\n- [GitHub Releases](/docs/getting-started/installation)\\n- [Website](https://rayforge.org/)\\n\\n## Join the Community\\n\\n- [Discord](https://discord.gg/sTHNdTtpQJ)\\n- [Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/c/knipknap)"},{"id":"rayforge-1.4-rotary-pdf-camera","metadata":{"permalink":"/fr/blog/rayforge-1.4-rotary-pdf-camera","source":"@site/blog/2026-03-29-rayforge-1.4-rotary-pdf-camera.md","title":"Rayforge 1.4 - Rotary Axis, PDF Layers, Camera Calibration","description":"Rayforge 1.4 adds rotary axis support for cylindrical workpieces, PDF vector import with layers, camera calibration, and improved sketcher tools.","date":"2026-03-29T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"1.4","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/1-4"},{"inline":true,"label":"rotary","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/rotary"},{"inline":true,"label":"camera","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/camera"},{"inline":true,"label":"pdf","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/pdf"},{"inline":true,"label":"sketcher","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/sketcher"}],"readingTime":2.87,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Rayforge Team","title":"Core development team","url":"https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge","imageURL":"/fr/images/icon.svg","key":"rayforge_team","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"rayforge-1.4-rotary-pdf-camera","title":"Rayforge 1.4 - Rotary Axis, PDF Layers, Camera Calibration","authors":"rayforge_team","tags":["release","1.4","rotary","camera","pdf","sketcher"],"description":"Rayforge 1.4 adds rotary axis support for cylindrical workpieces, PDF vector import with layers, camera calibration, and improved sketcher tools."},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.5 - 3D Simulator, Bezier Curves, No-Go Zones","permalink":"/fr/blog/rayforge-1.5-3d-simulator-bezier-nogozones"},"nextItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.3 - Bezier Curves in Sketcher, Modular Architecture","permalink":"/fr/blog/rayforge-1.3-bezier-curves-sketcher-addon"}},"content":"Rayforge 1.4 adds rotary axis support for cylindrical workpieces, direct\\nvector import for PDF files with layers, a guided camera calibration wizard,\\nand an improved sketcher with ellipse tools and smarter snapping.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Rotary Axis Support\\n\\nYou can now engrave and cut cylindrical objects like tumblers, glasses, and\\npens. Rayforge wraps your design around the cylinder surface and shows a 3D\\npreview so you know exactly what the result will look like before you start.\\n\\nRotary mode can be toggled per layer, which means you can combine flat and\\ncylindrical work in a single project. A small rotary icon next to each layer\\nmakes it easy to see which layers will run on the rotary attachment.\\n\\nHead over to the [Rotary Setup](../docs/machine/rotary) page for details on\\nconfiguring your module.\\n\\n## PDF Import with Layers\\n\\nPDF files can now be imported as vector paths instead of being rasterized\\nfirst. This means cleaner lines, no quality loss, and \u2014 if the PDF contains\\nlayers \u2014 you can pick which layers to import, just like with SVG files.\\n\\nThis is especially handy when someone sends you a PDF that was exported from\\nIllustrator or Inkscape and you need clean cutting paths without re-drawing\\nanything.\\n\\n## Camera Calibration Wizard\\n\\nGetting a camera aligned to your laser bed just got easier. The new guided\\ncalibration wizard walks you through the process step by step using a printed\\ncalibration card. Rayforge computes a full distortion model from the card\\nimages, correcting for barrel distortion and perspective errors automatically.\\n\\nThe result is noticeably better alignment accuracy, especially with wide-angle\\nlenses or cameras mounted at an angle.\\n\\n## Sketcher Improvements\\n\\nThe circle tool has been replaced with a more general **ellipse tool** that\\nhandles both circles and ellipses. The equality constraint now works on\\nellipses too.\\n\\nDrawing geometry also feels smoother now: many tools automatically apply\\nconstraints as you create shapes, and a new **magnetic snap** system replaces\\nthe old snap-to-grid behavior. Instead of locking to a fixed grid, magnetic\\nsnap pulls your cursor toward nearby geometry \u2014 points, lines, and endpoints \u2014\\nmaking it much easier to connect shapes precisely.\\n\\n## Better Framing Controls\\n\\nThe framing feature has new settings for finer control:\\n\\n- **Frame speed** is now configured per laser head\\n- **Corner dwell time** lets the laser pause briefly at each corner so you can\\n  see exactly where the boundary is\\n- **Repeat count** traces the outline multiple times for better visibility\\n\\n## Merge Lines Post-Processor\\n\\nA new post-processor called **Merge Lines** detects overlapping path segments\\nand merges them into a single pass. This is useful when you import designs\\nwhere shapes share edges \u2014 think grid patterns or tessellations \u2014 and you want\\nto avoid cutting the same line twice.\\n\\n## Other Improvements\\n\\n- Machine profile for the Acmer S1 has been added\\n- G-code dialects are now independent copies, so customizing one never affects\\n  others\\n- Dialects support a separate laser-on command for focusing\\n- Large images are handled more safely to prevent running out of memory\\n\\n## Bug Fixes\\n\\n- Fixed material test producer issues\\n- Fixed position reporting for machines with only X and Y axes\\n- Fixed a sketcher issue where distance constraints could shadow the line\\n  underneath\\n- Fixed memory exhaustion when importing very large images\\n- Fixed a race condition during worker initialization\\n\\nSee the CHANGELOG on GitHub for the complete list.\\n\\n## Download Rayforge 1.4\\n\\n- [GitHub Releases](/docs/getting-started/installation)\\n- [Website](https://rayforge.org/)\\n\\n## Join the Community\\n\\n- [Discord](https://discord.gg/sTHNdTtpQJ)\\n- [Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/c/knipknap)"},{"id":"rayforge-1.3-bezier-curves-sketcher-addon","metadata":{"permalink":"/fr/blog/rayforge-1.3-bezier-curves-sketcher-addon","source":"@site/blog/2026-03-23-rayforge-1.3-bezier-curves-sketcher-addon.md","title":"Rayforge 1.3 - Bezier Curves in Sketcher, Modular Architecture","description":"Rayforge 1.3 adds bezier curve support in the sketcher, a unified path tool, more efficient G-code output, and moves the sketcher to an add-on.","date":"2026-03-23T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"1.3","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/1-3"},{"inline":true,"label":"sketcher","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/sketcher"},{"inline":true,"label":"bezier","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/bezier"},{"inline":true,"label":"addons","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/addons"}],"readingTime":2.68,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Rayforge Team","title":"Core development team","url":"https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge","imageURL":"/fr/images/icon.svg","key":"rayforge_team","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"rayforge-1.3-bezier-curves-sketcher-addon","title":"Rayforge 1.3 - Bezier Curves in Sketcher, Modular Architecture","authors":"rayforge_team","tags":["release","1.3","sketcher","bezier","addons"],"description":"Rayforge 1.3 adds bezier curve support in the sketcher, a unified path tool, more efficient G-code output, and moves the sketcher to an add-on."},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.4 - Rotary Axis, PDF Layers, Camera Calibration","permalink":"/fr/blog/rayforge-1.4-rotary-pdf-camera"},"nextItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.2 - AI Generator, Camera Enhancements, and Improved Add-ons","permalink":"/fr/blog/rayforge-1.2-addons-camera-ai"}},"content":"Rayforge 1.3 brings bezier curve support to the parametric sketcher, a new\\nunified path tool, more efficient G-code output, and moves the sketcher to\\nan optional add-on.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Bezier Curves in the Sketcher\\n\\nThe headline feature for this release is full support for bezier curves in\\nthe parametric sketcher. The old line tool has been replaced with a new\\nunified **path tool** that seamlessly combines lines and curves.\\n\\nYou can now:\\n\\n- Draw smooth bezier curves with intuitive handle-based editing\\n- Connect curves to existing geometry - the path edit tool can snap to\\n  existing points in your sketch\\n- Make endpoints smooth or symmetric when they\'re connected by a coincident\\n  constraint - perfect for creating seamless curves\\n- Convert bezier curves back to straight lines with the new \\"straighten\\"\\n  tool\\n\\nThis has been one of the most requested features, and we\'re excited to see\\nwhat you create with it.\\n\\n## Sketcher is Now an Add-on\\n\\nContinuing the modularization work from version 1.2, the sketcher has been\\nmoved to an add-on. It\'s installed and enabled by default, so existing users\\nwon\'t notice any difference. But if you prefer a minimal setup without\\nparametric sketching, you can now disable it.\\n\\nThis change also comes with new extension registries that make it easier for\\nadd-on developers to extend Rayforge.\\n\\n## Sketcher Quality-of-Life Improvements\\n\\nThe sketcher received several smaller but impactful improvements:\\n\\n**Grid Tool**\\nA new tool to toggle grid visibility for better alignment.\\n\\n**Conflicting Constraints**\\nWhen constraints conflict with each other, they\'re now highlighted in the\\npanel so you can quickly identify and fix the problem.\\n\\n**Show/Hide Controls**\\nNew toggle buttons let you show or hide construction geometry and constraints\\nindividually.\\n\\n**Shift Constrains Movement**\\nHold Shift while dragging to constrain movement to the nearest axis - great\\nfor keeping things aligned.\\n\\n**Cleaner Background**\\nThe gray background area is now hidden for a cleaner editing experience.\\n\\n## More Efficient G-code\\n\\nRayforge now produces more compact G-code by omitting unchanged coordinates.\\nIf you\'re cutting along the X-axis, for example, only the X coordinate will\\nbe emitted on each line. This makes files smaller and cleaner, and makes\\nthe old \\"no-Z\\" dialect variants obsolete (they\'ve been removed).\\n\\nThe G-code viewer also got some updates:\\n\\n- Shows line count and byte size\\n- Always displays at least the first 20,000 lines\\n\\n## Raster Operation Enhancements\\n\\nNew settings for sample interval and power levels give you more control over\\nyour raster operations. These are particularly useful for fine-tuning results\\non materials that need precise power management.\\n\\n## Other Improvements\\n\\n- All icons normalized to 32x32 viewbox for consistent appearance\\n- AI workpiece generator now creates sketches when the geometry can be mapped\\n- Updated translations\\n\\n## Bug Fixes\\n\\nThis release fixes many issues:\\n\\n- Fixed fillet and chamfer tools not working correctly\\n- Fixed texture encoder drawing spaced dots instead of lines in some cases\\n- Fixed G1 being emitted without coordinates when all coordinates were unchanged\\n- Fixed loading project files with unknown assets\\n- Fixed issues when disabling and re-enabling add-ons at runtime\\n\\nSee the CHANGELOG on GitHub for the complete list.\\n\\n## Download Rayforge 1.3\\n\\n- [GitHub Releases](/docs/getting-started/installation)\\n- [Website](https://rayforge.org/)\\n\\n## Join the Community\\n\\n- [Discord](https://discord.gg/sTHNdTtpQJ)\\n- [Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/c/knipknap)"},{"id":"rayforge-1.2-addons-camera-ai","metadata":{"permalink":"/fr/blog/rayforge-1.2-addons-camera-ai","source":"@site/blog/2026-03-10-rayforge-1.2-addons-camera-ai.md","title":"Rayforge 1.2 - AI Generator, Camera Enhancements, and Improved Add-ons","description":"Rayforge 1.2 adds an AI workpiece generator for laser design, camera calibration improvements, and a modular add-on system for laser cutting workflows.","date":"2026-03-10T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"1.2","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/1-2"},{"inline":true,"label":"addons","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/addons"},{"inline":true,"label":"camera","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/camera"},{"inline":true,"label":"ai","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/ai"}],"readingTime":3.36,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Rayforge Team","title":"Core development team","url":"https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge","imageURL":"/fr/images/icon.svg","key":"rayforge_team","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"rayforge-1.2-addons-camera-ai","title":"Rayforge 1.2 - AI Generator, Camera Enhancements, and Improved Add-ons","authors":"rayforge_team","tags":["release","1.2","addons","camera","ai"],"description":"Rayforge 1.2 adds an AI workpiece generator for laser design, camera calibration improvements, and a modular add-on system for laser cutting workflows."},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.3 - Bezier Curves in Sketcher, Modular Architecture","permalink":"/fr/blog/rayforge-1.3-bezier-curves-sketcher-addon"},"nextItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.1 - MacOS Support, Pipeline Rewrite, G-code Console, and Unified Raster","permalink":"/fr/blog/rayforge-1.1-pipeline-rewrite"}},"content":"Rayforge 1.2 brings an AI workpiece generator, significant camera\\nenhancements, and a completely revamped add-on system with core\\nfunctionality now available as optional modules.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## AI Workpiece Generator Add-on\\n\\nA new experimental add-on allows generating workpieces from text prompts.\\nThis is great for quickly creating simple designs or getting inspiration\\nfor new projects.\\n\\nThis is a first step, and we\'re excited about the possibilities this\\nopens up for the future!\\n\\n## Camera Enhancements\\n\\nThanks to the incredible work of **MausRundung**, the camera system has\\nreceived a major overhaul:\\n\\n### Image Enhancement\\n\\n- Temporal noise reduction with configurable strength\\n- Cleaner preview images, especially in low-light conditions\\n\\n### Fisheye Distortion Correction\\n\\n- Radial distortion correction (k1, k2 parameters)\\n- Tangential distortion correction (p1, p2 parameters)\\n- Perfect for wide-angle lenses\\n\\n### Improved Alignment UI\\n\\n- Zoom, pan, and keyboard navigation in the alignment dialog\\n- Better point dragging with visual feedback\\n- Image stretching and positioning controls with offsets\\n\\n## Improved Add-on System\\n\\nThe add-on system has been greatly improved. The main change is that much\\nof the core functionality has been moved into add-ons that are installed\\nby default, but can be disabled or enabled as needed:\\n\\n**Core as Add-ons**\\nThe built-in transformers and laser essentials have been converted to\\nadd-ons. This makes Rayforge more modular - you can disable features you\\ndon\'t need or enable only what you want.\\n\\n**Add-on Capabilities**\\nAdd-ons can now:\\n- Register transformers (post-processors) for custom G-code manipulation\\n- Register keyboard shortcuts for custom workflows\\n- Hook into the backend and frontend independently\\n\\n**Commercial Support**\\nThe system now supports paid and third-party add-ons, enabling developers\\nto create commercial extensions for Rayforge.\\n\\n## Stock Improvements\\n\\nStock handling is now more flexible:\\n\\n- **Document-level stock** - stock is no longer tied to individual layers\\n- **Duplicate stock** using Ctrl+D\\n- **Non-rectangular stock** - convert any workpiece to stock for irregular\\n  materials\\n\\n## Sketcher Improvements\\n\\nThe parametric sketcher received several quality-of-life improvements in\\nthis release:\\n\\n- **Live preview for line tool** - see the line before you commit\\n- **Dimension display** - shows dimensions while adding geometry\\n- **Snap-to-grid** - hold Ctrl to snap to the grid\\n- **Entity highlighting** - hovered entities and constraints are highlighted\\n- **Toolbar shortcuts** - shows currently available keyboard shortcuts\\n- **Connected selection** - Shift+Double click selects connected geometry\\n- **Arc radius adjustment** - change arc radius while adding the second endpoint\\n\\n## More New Features\\n\\n### Crop to Stock Post-Processor\\n\\nA new post-processor that automatically crops operations to your stock\\nboundaries, saving time and material.\\n\\n### Inter-Workpiece Path Optimization\\n\\nThe path optimizer now also optimizes the workpiece order, reducing travel\\ndistance when working with multiple workpieces in a single job. Previously,\\nRayforge only optimized travel paths within individual workpieces.\\n\\n### Configurable Cut/Raster Colors\\n\\nEach laser can now have its own cut and raster colors, making it easier\\nto distinguish between different laser heads.\\n\\n### Quick WCS Positioning\\n\\nClick anywhere on the canvas to set the work coordinate system origin.\\n\\n### OMTech K40+ Profile\\n\\nNew machine profile for the popular OMTech K40+ laser cutter.\\n\\n### Mach4 G-code Dialect\\n\\nNew built-in G-code dialect for Mach4 controllers using M67 for spindle\\nspeed (laser power) control.\\n\\n### Platform Updates\\n\\n- Updated macOS support thanks to **Pablo Gil**\\n- Flatpak updates thanks to **fllmn**\\n\\n## Bug Fixes\\n\\nThis release addresses many issues:\\n\\n- Add-on not enabled immediately after installation\\n- macOS bundle issues with GTK modules and built-in add-ons\\n- Tasker startup crash with DictProxy type annotations\\n- Old project files not showing new transformers\\n- SVG exporter stacking multiple workpieces on top of each other\\n- Auto layout for rotated stock\\n- Windows build using wrong version string on forks\\n- Mac and Windows builds not finding icon\\n\\nSee the CHANGELOG on GitHub for the complete list.\\n\\n## Special Thanks\\n\\nThis release was made possible with the support of our Patreon supporters:\\n\\n- 2 anonymous contributors\\n- Amsel\\n- froqstar\\n\\nAnd thanks to **MausRundung** for the camera enhancements, **Pablo Gil** for\\nmacOS updates, and **fllmn** for Flatpak updates!\\n\\n## Download Rayforge 1.2\\n\\n- [GitHub Releases](https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge/releases)\\n- [Website](https://rayforge.org/)\\n\\n## Join the Community\\n\\n- [Discord](https://discord.gg/sTHNdTtpQJ)\\n- [Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/c/knipknap)"},{"id":"rayforge-1.1-pipeline-rewrite","metadata":{"permalink":"/fr/blog/rayforge-1.1-pipeline-rewrite","source":"@site/blog/2026-02-27-rayforge-1.1-pipeline-rewrite.md","title":"Rayforge 1.1 - MacOS Support, Pipeline Rewrite, G-code Console, and Unified Raster","description":"Rayforge 1.1 brings macOS support, a new G-code console, unified raster operations, and a rewritten pipeline for better laser cutting performance.","date":"2026-02-27T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"1.1","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/1-1"},{"inline":true,"label":"pipeline","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/pipeline"},{"inline":true,"label":"raster","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/raster"},{"inline":true,"label":"gcode","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/gcode"}],"readingTime":2.48,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Rayforge Team","title":"Core development team","url":"https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge","imageURL":"/fr/images/icon.svg","key":"rayforge_team","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"rayforge-1.1-pipeline-rewrite","title":"Rayforge 1.1 - MacOS Support, Pipeline Rewrite, G-code Console, and Unified Raster","authors":"rayforge_team","tags":["release","1.1","pipeline","raster","gcode"],"description":"Rayforge 1.1 brings macOS support, a new G-code console, unified raster operations, and a rewritten pipeline for better laser cutting performance."},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.2 - AI Generator, Camera Enhancements, and Improved Add-ons","permalink":"/fr/blog/rayforge-1.2-addons-camera-ai"},"nextItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.0 - C\xe9l\xe9bration du premier anniversaire","permalink":"/fr/blog/rayforge-1.0-first-birthday"}},"content":"![Rayforge 1.1](/images/rayforge-1.1.png)\\n\\nRayforge 1.1 brings a powerful new G-code console, unified raster operations,\\nand a completely rebuilt data pipeline for improved performance and stability.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## MacOS Support\\n\\nThanks to the incredible work of GitHub user **pgilfernandez**, Rayforge\\nnow officially supports macOS! Both Intel and Apple Silicon Macs are\\nsupported. This has been a long-requested feature, and we\'re thrilled to\\nwelcome Mac users to the Rayforge community.\\n\\n## The Big Story: Complete Pipeline Rewrite\\n\\nThe headline feature of this release is a complete rewrite of the data\\npipeline backend. The new architecture is based on a Directed Acyclic Graph\\n(DAG), which brings significant improvements:\\n\\n- **Better performance** for complex projects with many operations\\n- **Reduced memory usage** through more efficient data handling\\n- **Smoother UI responsiveness** during heavy processing\\n- **Fixed memory leaks** that affected long editing sessions\\n\\nThis foundational upgrade makes Rayforge more robust and prepares the\\ncodebase for future features.\\n\\n## Unified Raster Operations\\n\\nThe old \\"raster\\", \\"depth\\", and \\"dither\\" operations have been merged into a\\nsingle, unified raster operation. This simplifies the workflow while giving\\nyou more control:\\n\\n- **Configurable line distance** in all raster operations\\n- **New \\"Raster (Dither)\\" operation** with configurable algorithms\\n- **Auto thresholding** for Variable Power and Multipass modes\\n- **Histogram** in the raster engraver for visual threshold setting\\n- **Symbolic visualization** of raster direction in the rasterizer\\n\\n## G-code Console\\n\\nThe log view has been replaced with a fully-featured G-code terminal. You can\\nnow send commands directly to your machine, view responses in real-time, and\\ninteract with your laser cutter more directly than ever before.\\n\\n## More New Features\\n\\n### Export Support\\n\\nYou can now export your documents or selected objects to SVG and DXF formats.\\nThis is great for sharing designs or using them in other software.\\n\\n### Sketcher Improvements\\n\\n- **Angle constraints** are now available in the parametric sketcher\\n- **Conflicting constraints** are highlighted in red for easier debugging\\n\\n### Machine Configuration\\n\\n- Axis extents, work surface, and soft limits can now be configured per machine\\n- Built-in G-code dialect supporting dynamic power mode\\n\\n### Other Additions\\n\\n- Increased maximum laser spot size to 10 mm\\n- `RAYFORGE_MAX_WORKERS` environment variable to limit processes\\n- macOS packaging scripts and resources for better platform support\\n- `--uiscript` CLI argument for executing scripts after the UI is up\\n\\n## Bug Fixes\\n\\nThis release addresses many issues:\\n\\n- Multiple memory leaks in the data pipeline\\n- Race conditions between worker pool task completion and pipeline shutdown\\n- Camera device scanning crash on Windows\\n- Multipass post-processor exception\\n- Rasterizer angle causing distortion\\n- Various macOS issues: shm_open length errors, SVG rendering fallback,\\n  keyboard shortcuts\\n- Workpiece stage not emitting correct node state\\n- Zoom resolution stuck until resizing at least once\\n- Blurry view overlay on startup\\n- Unresponsive serial ports now handled gracefully\\n\\n## Special Thanks\\n\\nThis release was made possible with the support of our Patreon supporters:\\n\\n- 2 anonymous contributors\\n- Amsel\\n\\nThank you for supporting Rayforge development!\\n\\n## Download Rayforge 1.1\\n\\n- [GitHub Releases](https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge/releases)\\n- [Website](https://rayforge.org/)\\n\\n## Join the Community\\n\\n- [Discord](https://discord.gg/sTHNdTtpQJ)\\n- [Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/c/knipknap)"},{"id":"rayforge-1.0-first-birthday","metadata":{"permalink":"/fr/blog/rayforge-1.0-first-birthday","source":"@site/i18n/fr/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2026-01-29-rayforge-1.0-first-birthday.md","title":"Rayforge 1.0 - C\xe9l\xe9bration du premier anniversaire","description":"Rayforge 1.0","date":"2026-01-29T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"version","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/version"},{"inline":true,"label":"1","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/1"},{"inline":true,"label":"\xe9tape","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/etape"}],"readingTime":3.81,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Rayforge Team","title":"Core development team","url":"https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge","imageURL":"/fr/images/icon.svg","key":"rayforge_team","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"rayforge-1.0-first-birthday","title":"Rayforge 1.0 - C\xe9l\xe9bration du premier anniversaire","authors":"rayforge_team","tags":["version","1","\xe9tape"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.1 - MacOS Support, Pipeline Rewrite, G-code Console, and Unified Raster","permalink":"/fr/blog/rayforge-1.1-pipeline-rewrite"},"nextItem":{"title":"5 conseils pour de meilleurs r\xe9sultats de gravure laser avec Rayforge","permalink":"/fr/blog/5-tips-better-engraving"}},"content":"![Rayforge 1.0](/images/rayforge-1.0.png)\\n\\nAujourd\'hui marque une \xe9tape sp\xe9ciale pour Rayforge - nous publions la\\nversion 1.0 exactement le jour du premier anniversaire du projet ! Ce qui\\na commenc\xe9 par un simple commit le 1er f\xe9vrier 2025 s\'est transform\xe9 en\\nune plateforme compl\xe8te de d\xe9coupe et gravure laser.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Le parcours jusqu\'ici\\n\\nAu cours de l\'ann\xe9e \xe9coul\xe9e, Rayforge est pass\xe9 d\'un outil basique de\\ncontr\xf4le laser \xe0 une plateforme compl\xe8te de conception et fabrication.\\nNous avons tout construit \xe0 partir de z\xe9ro : un syst\xe8me de CAO 2D\\nparam\xe9trique, un aper\xe7u 3D du G-code, la prise en charge multi-couches,\\nla prise en charge multi-laser, l\'alignement par cam\xe9ra, les syst\xe8mes de\\ncoordonn\xe9es de travail, et bien plus encore.\\n\\nCette version repr\xe9sente l\'aboutissement de cette vision - un outil\\nstable et pr\xeat pour la production capable de g\xe9rer de vrais flux de\\ntravail de d\xe9coupe et gravure laser.\\n\\n## Quoi de neuf dans la 1.0\\n\\n### Sauvegarde et chargement de projets\\n\\nLa fonctionnalit\xe9 la plus demand\xe9e est enfin l\xe0. Vous pouvez maintenant\\nsauvegarder vos flux de travail complets et les restaurer ult\xe9rieurement.\\nLes extensions de fichiers `.ryp` (projet) et `.rfs` (esquisse) sont\\nenregistr\xe9es au niveau du syst\xe8me, vous pouvez donc double-cliquer sur\\nvos projets pour les ouvrir directement. Un menu de fichiers r\xe9cents\\nfournit un acc\xe8s rapide \xe0 votre travail.\\n\\n### Esquisseur param\xe9trique avec prise en charge du texte\\n\\nL\'esquisseur prend d\xe9sormais en charge le texte avec une int\xe9gration\\ncompl\xe8te des contraintes. Ajoutez du texte \xe0 vos esquisses, appliquez\\ndes contraintes de rapport d\'aspect, et contr\xf4lez le placement et le\\ndimensionnement de mani\xe8re param\xe9trique. Cela ouvre tout un monde de\\npossibilit\xe9s de conception pour les enseignes grav\xe9es au laser, les\\n\xe9tiquettes et les \xe9l\xe9ments d\xe9coratifs.\\n\\n### Panneau inf\xe9rieur unifi\xe9\\n\\nLe dialogue de d\xe9placement et la vue du journal ont \xe9t\xe9 fusionn\xe9s en\\nun seul panneau inf\xe9rieur unifi\xe9. Cette consolidation offre un espace\\nde travail plus propre tout en gardant les outils essentiels de contr\xf4le\\net de surveillance de la machine facilement accessibles. Le panneau\\ncomporte un acc\xe8s par onglets aux contr\xf4les de d\xe9placement et \xe0 la\\nsortie du journal, facilitant le basculement entre les op\xe9rations sans\\nperdre d\'espace d\'\xe9cran.\\n\\n### Autres am\xe9liorations\\n\\n- **Panneau inf\xe9rieur** : Le dialogue de d\xe9placement et la vue du journal\\n  sont maintenant fusionn\xe9s dans un panneau inf\xe9rieur unifi\xe9\\n- **Dialogue d\'importation** : Les erreurs sont maintenant collect\xe9es et\\n  affich\xe9es ensemble\\n- **Importateurs** : Presque enti\xe8rement r\xe9\xe9crits pour une meilleure\\n  testabilit\xe9\\n- **Stabilit\xe9 de l\'esquisseur** : Le solveur favorise maintenant les points\\n  pour un d\xe9placement plus stable\\n- **Corrections de bugs** : Import DXF multi-couches, bugs d\'alignement,\\n  probl\xe8mes de centrage, et plus encore\\n\\n## Points forts des fonctionnalit\xe9s\\n\\nRayforge 1.0 comprend plus de 60 fonctionnalit\xe9s :\\n\\n**Outils de conception**\\n\\n- CAO 2D avec esquisse param\xe9trique\\n- Contraintes g\xe9om\xe9triques et dimensionnelles\\n- Prise en charge du texte dans les esquisses\\n- Prise en charge multi-couches\\n\\n**Fabrication**\\n\\n- Op\xe9rations 2.5D (contour, trame, gravure en profondeur)\\n- Prise en charge multi-laser\\n- Syst\xe8mes de coordonn\xe9es de travail (G54-G59)\\n- Optimisation et lissage des trajets\\n- Ponts de maintien avec placement automatique\\n\\n**Import/Export**\\n\\n- Prise en charge des fichiers SVG, DXF, PDF, JPEG, PNG, BMP, Ruida\\n- Tra\xe7age vectoriel avec plusieurs algorithmes\\n- Pr\xe9traitement d\'image (d\xe9bruitage, inversion, seuillage)\\n\\n**Contr\xf4le de machine**\\n\\n- Profils multi-machines\\n- Param\xe8tres de firmware pour GRBL, Smoothieware, Marlin\\n- Macros et hooks G-code\\n- Substitution de variables\\n- Console terminal avec statut en direct\\n\\n**Visualisation**\\n\\n- Aper\xe7u 3D du G-code avec simulation compl\xe8te\\n- Alignement par cam\xe9ra\\n- Th\xe8mes sombre et clair\\n- Prise en charge multilingue\\n\\n## Un regard en arri\xe8re\\n\\nLe premier commit a \xe9t\xe9 fait le 1er f\xe9vrier 2025, \xe0 19:37:27. C\'\xe9tait un\\nsimple \xab import initial \xbb avec un support de rendu SVG basique. Depuis\\nlors, nous avons :\\n\\n- Publi\xe9 28 versions (0.13 \xe0 0.28, plus 1.0)\\n- Ajout\xe9 plus de 60 fonctionnalit\xe9s\\n- Corrig\xe9 des centaines de bugs\\n- Construit une communaut\xe9 d\'utilisateurs et de contributeurs\\n- Cr\xe9\xe9 des installateurs pour Windows, Linux (deb, snap, flatpak) et macOS\\n\\n## Et maintenant ?\\n\\nLa version 1.0 est une \xe9tape, pas une destination. La feuille de route\\n\xe0 venir comprend :\\n\\n- Outils vectoriels et capacit\xe9s d\'\xe9dition am\xe9lior\xe9s\\n- Support mat\xe9riel plus large\\n- Optimisations de performance pour les grands projets\\n- Plus de profils de machine et de dialectes\\n- \xc9cosyst\xe8me de paquets pilot\xe9 par la communaut\xe9\\n\\n## T\xe9l\xe9charger Rayforge 1.0\\n\\nObtenez la derni\xe8re version depuis notre site web : https://rayforge.org/\\n\\nLes installateurs sont disponibles pour :\\n\\n- Windows (installateur)\\n- Linux (deb, snap, flatpak)\\n- macOS (dmg)\\n\\n## Rejoignez la communaut\xe9\\n\\n- **GitHub** : https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge\\n- **Discord** : https://discord.gg/sTHNdTtpQJ\\n- **Patreon** : https://www.patreon.com/c/knipknap\\n\\nMerci \xe0 tous ceux qui ont contribu\xe9, test\xe9, signal\xe9 des bugs, ou\\nsimplement utilis\xe9 Rayforge au cours de cette ann\xe9e pass\xe9e. Voici une\\nnouvelle ann\xe9e \xe0 construire l\'avenir de la fabrication open-source !\\n\\n---\\n\\n*Joyeux premier anniversaire, Rayforge ! \ud83c\udf82*"},{"id":"5-tips-better-engraving","metadata":{"permalink":"/fr/blog/5-tips-better-engraving","source":"@site/i18n/fr/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2025-02-20-5-tips-better-engraving.md","title":"5 conseils pour de meilleurs r\xe9sultats de gravure laser avec Rayforge","description":"Aper\xe7u 3D","date":"2025-02-20T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"gravure","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/gravure"},{"inline":true,"label":"optimisation","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/optimisation"},{"inline":true,"label":"qualit\xe9","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/qualite"},{"inline":true,"label":"flux-de-travail","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/flux-de-travail"}],"readingTime":4.28,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Rayforge Team","title":"Core development team","url":"https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge","imageURL":"/fr/images/icon.svg","key":"rayforge_team","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"5-tips-better-engraving","title":"5 conseils pour de meilleurs r\xe9sultats de gravure laser avec Rayforge","authors":"rayforge_team","tags":["gravure","optimisation","qualit\xe9","flux-de-travail"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.0 - C\xe9l\xe9bration du premier anniversaire","permalink":"/fr/blog/rayforge-1.0-first-birthday"},"nextItem":{"title":"Prise en charge multi-laser - Choisissez diff\xe9rents lasers pour chaque op\xe9ration","permalink":"/fr/blog/multi-laser-support"}},"content":"![Aper\xe7u 3D](/screenshots/main-3d.png)\\n\\nObtenir des r\xe9sultats de gravure laser de qualit\xe9 professionnelle\\nn\xe9cessite plus que du bon mat\xe9riel \u2014 vos param\xe8tres logiciels et votre\\nflux de travail comptent aussi. Voici cinq conseils pour vous aider \xe0\\ntirer le meilleur parti de Rayforge.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## 1. Utilisez l\'overscan pour une gravure tram\xe9e plus fluide\\n\\nLors de la gravure tram\xe9e, un probl\xe8me courant est l\'apparition de\\nlignes visibles ou d\'incoh\xe9rences sur les bords o\xf9 le laser change de\\ndirection. Cela se produit parce que la t\xeate laser doit d\xe9c\xe9l\xe9rer et\\nacc\xe9l\xe9rer, ce qui peut affecter la qualit\xe9 de gravure.\\n\\n**Solution** : Activez l\'**Overscan** dans les param\xe8tres de votre\\nop\xe9ration tram\xe9e.\\n\\nL\'overscan \xe9tend le trajet du laser au-del\xe0 de la zone de gravure\\nr\xe9elle, permettant \xe0 la t\xeate d\'atteindre sa pleine vitesse avant\\nd\'entrer dans la zone de travail et de la maintenir tout au long.\\nCela donne une gravure beaucoup plus fluide et plus homog\xe8ne.\\n\\nPour activer l\'overscan :\\n\\n1. S\xe9lectionnez votre op\xe9ration tram\xe9e\\n2. Ouvrez les param\xe8tres de l\'op\xe9ration\\n3. Activez \xab Overscan \xbb et d\xe9finissez la distance (g\xe9n\xe9ralement 3-5mm\\n   fonctionne bien)\\n\\nEn savoir plus dans notre [guide Overscan](/docs/features/overscan).\\n\\n## 2. Optimisez le temps de d\xe9placement avec l\'ordonnancement des trajets\\n\\nPour les op\xe9rations de contour avec de nombreux trajets s\xe9par\xe9s,\\nl\'ordre dans lequel le laser visite chaque forme peut avoir un impact\\nsignificatif sur le temps total de la t\xe2che.\\n\\n**Solution** : Utilisez l\'**optimisation du temps de d\xe9placement**\\nint\xe9gr\xe9e de Rayforge.\\n\\nRayforge peut r\xe9organiser automatiquement les trajets pour minimiser\\nle temps de d\xe9placement sans d\xe9coupe. Cela est particuli\xe8rement utile\\npour les t\xe2ches avec de nombreux petits objets ou du texte avec\\nplusieurs lettres.\\n\\nL\'optimisation des trajets est g\xe9n\xe9ralement activ\xe9e par d\xe9faut, mais\\nvous pouvez la v\xe9rifier et l\'ajuster dans les param\xe8tres de l\'op\xe9ration\\nContour.\\n\\n## 3. Ajoutez des ponts de maintien pour \xe9viter le d\xe9placement des pi\xe8ces\\n\\nRien n\'est plus frustrant que de voir une t\xe2che de d\xe9coupe presque\\ntermin\xe9e g\xe2ch\xe9e parce que la pi\xe8ce a boug\xe9 ou est tomb\xe9e \xe0 travers le\\nplateau de la machine au dernier moment.\\n\\n**Solution** : Utilisez des **Ponts de maintien** pour garder les pi\xe8ces\\nen place jusqu\'\xe0 ce que la t\xe2che soit termin\xe9e.\\n\\nLes ponts de maintien sont de petites sections non d\xe9coup\xe9es qui\\nmaintiennent votre pi\xe8ce connect\xe9e au mat\xe9riau environnant. Une fois\\nla t\xe2che termin\xe9e, vous pouvez facilement retirer la pi\xe8ce et nettoyer\\nles ponts avec un couteau ou du papier de verre.\\n\\nRayforge prend en charge le placement manuel et automatique des ponts :\\n\\n- **Manuel** : Cliquez exactement o\xf9 vous voulez les ponts sur le canevas\\n- **Automatique** : Sp\xe9cifiez le nombre de ponts et laissez Rayforge\\n  les r\xe9partir uniform\xe9ment\\n\\nConsultez la [documentation des Ponts de maintien](/docs/features/holding-tabs)\\npour un guide complet.\\n\\n## 4. Pr\xe9visualisez votre t\xe2che en 3D avant l\'ex\xe9cution\\n\\nL\'une des fonctionnalit\xe9s les plus pr\xe9cieuses de Rayforge est l\'aper\xe7u\\n3D du G-code. Il est tentant de sauter cette \xe9tape et d\'envoyer la\\nt\xe2che directement \xe0 la machine, mais prendre un moment pour pr\xe9visualiser\\npeut vous faire gagner du temps et des mat\xe9riaux.\\n\\n**Ce qu\'il faut rechercher dans l\'aper\xe7u** :\\n\\n- V\xe9rifiez que toutes les op\xe9rations s\'ex\xe9cutent dans le bon ordre\\n- Recherchez tout trajet d\'outil ou chevauchement inattendu\\n- Confirmez que les op\xe9rations multi-passes ont le nombre correct de passes\\n- Assurez-vous que les limites de la t\xe2che s\'inscrivent dans votre mat\xe9riau\\n\\nPour ouvrir l\'aper\xe7u 3D, cliquez sur le bouton **Aper\xe7u 3D** dans la\\nbarre d\'outils principale apr\xe8s avoir g\xe9n\xe9r\xe9 votre G-code.\\n\\nEn savoir plus sur l\'aper\xe7u 3D dans notre\\n[documentation de l\'interface](/docs/ui/3d-preview).\\n\\n## 5. Utilisez des hooks G-code personnalis\xe9s pour des flux de travail coh\xe9rents\\n\\nSi vous vous retrouvez \xe0 ex\xe9cuter les m\xeames commandes G-code avant ou\\napr\xe8s chaque t\xe2che \u2014 comme le retour \xe0 l\'origine, l\'activation d\'une\\nassistance air, ou l\'ex\xe9cution d\'une routine de mise au point \u2014 vous\\npouvez automatiser cela avec des **Macros et Hooks G-code**.\\n\\n**Cas d\'utilisation courants** :\\n\\n- **Hook pr\xe9-t\xe2che** : Retour \xe0 l\'origine de la machine, activation de\\n  l\'assistance air, ex\xe9cution d\'une routine de mise au point automatique\\n- **Hook post-t\xe2che** : D\xe9sactivation de l\'assistance air, retour \xe0 la\\n  position d\'origine, lecture d\'un son de fin\\n- **Macros sp\xe9cifiques \xe0 une couche** : Changement de la hauteur de mise\\n  au point entre les op\xe9rations, changement de modules laser\\n\\nLes hooks prennent en charge la substitution de variables, vous pouvez\\ndonc r\xe9f\xe9rencer des propri\xe9t\xe9s de t\xe2che comme l\'\xe9paisseur du mat\xe9riau,\\nle type d\'op\xe9ration, et plus encore.\\n\\nExemple de hook pr\xe9-t\xe2che :\\n\\n```gcode\\nG28 ; Retour \xe0 l\'origine de tous les axes\\nM8 ; Activer l\'assistance air\\nG0 Z{focus_height} ; D\xe9placer \xe0 la hauteur de mise au point\\n```\\n\\nConsultez notre [guide des Macros et Hooks G-code](/docs/machine/hooks-macros)\\npour des exemples d\xe9taill\xe9s et une r\xe9f\xe9rence des variables.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Conseil bonus : Testez d\'abord sur du mat\xe9riel de r\xe9cup\xe9ration\\n\\nBien que cela ne soit pas sp\xe9cifique \xe0 Rayforge, cela vaut la peine d\'\xeatre\\nr\xe9p\xe9t\xe9 : testez toujours les nouveaux param\xe8tres, op\xe9rations ou mat\xe9riaux\\nsur des chutes d\'abord. Utilisez les profils de mat\xe9riaux et les pr\xe9r\xe9glages\\nd\'op\xe9rations de Rayforge pour sauvegarder vos param\xe8tres test\xe9s pour une\\nutilisation future.\\n\\n---\\n\\n*Vous avez vos propres astuces et conseils Rayforge ? Partagez-les avec\\nla communaut\xe9 sur [GitHub Discussions](https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge/discussions) !*"},{"id":"multi-laser-support","metadata":{"permalink":"/fr/blog/multi-laser-support","source":"@site/i18n/fr/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2025-01-10-multi-laser-support.md","title":"Prise en charge multi-laser - Choisissez diff\xe9rents lasers pour chaque op\xe9ration","description":"L\'une des fonctionnalit\xe9s les plus puissantes de Rayforge est la capacit\xe9","date":"2025-01-10T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"multi-laser","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/multi-laser"},{"inline":true,"label":"op\xe9rations","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/operations"},{"inline":true,"label":"flux-de-travail","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/flux-de-travail"}],"readingTime":3.01,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Rayforge Team","title":"Core development team","url":"https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge","imageURL":"/fr/images/icon.svg","key":"rayforge_team","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"multi-laser-support","title":"Prise en charge multi-laser - Choisissez diff\xe9rents lasers pour chaque op\xe9ration","authors":"rayforge_team","tags":["multi-laser","op\xe9rations","flux-de-travail"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"5 conseils pour de meilleurs r\xe9sultats de gravure laser avec Rayforge","permalink":"/fr/blog/5-tips-better-engraving"},"nextItem":{"title":"Bienvenue dans Rayforge : Logiciel de contr\xf4le laser moderne","permalink":"/fr/blog/welcome-to-rayforge"}},"content":"L\'une des fonctionnalit\xe9s les plus puissantes de Rayforge est la capacit\xe9\\nd\'assigner diff\xe9rents lasers \xe0 diff\xe9rentes op\xe9rations au sein d\'une m\xeame\\nt\xe2che. Cela ouvre des possibilit\xe9s passionnantes pour les configurations\\nmulti-outils et les flux de travail sp\xe9cialis\xe9s.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Qu\'est-ce que la prise en charge multi-laser ?\\n\\nSi votre machine est \xe9quip\xe9e de plusieurs modules laser \u2014 par exemple,\\nun laser \xe0 diode pour la gravure et un laser CO2 pour la d\xe9coupe, ou\\ndiff\xe9rents lasers \xe0 diode de puissance vari\xe9e optimis\xe9s pour diff\xe9rents\\nmat\xe9riaux \u2014 Rayforge vous permet de tirer pleinement parti de cette\\nconfiguration.\\n\\nAvec la prise en charge multi-laser, vous pouvez :\\n\\n- **Assigner diff\xe9rents lasers \xe0 diff\xe9rentes op\xe9rations** dans votre t\xe2che\\n- **Basculer entre les modules laser** automatiquement pendant l\'ex\xe9cution\\n  de la t\xe2che\\n- **Optimiser pour le mat\xe9riau et la t\xe2che** en utilisant l\'outil adapt\xe9\\n  \xe0 chaque op\xe9ration\\n\\n## Cas d\'utilisation\\n\\n### Gravure et d\xe9coupe hybrides\\n\\nImaginez que vous travailliez sur un projet de panneau en bois :\\n\\n1. **Op\xe9ration 1** : Utiliser un laser \xe0 diode de faible puissance pour\\n   graver du texte fin et des graphiques d\xe9taill\xe9s\\n2. **Op\xe9ration 2** : Passer \xe0 un laser CO2 de plus grande puissance pour\\n   d\xe9couper la forme du panneau\\n\\nAvec Rayforge, vous assignez simplement chaque op\xe9ration au laser\\nappropri\xe9 dans votre profil de machine, et le logiciel g\xe8re le reste.\\n\\n### Optimisation sp\xe9cifique au mat\xe9riau\\n\\nDiff\xe9rents types de laser excellent avec diff\xe9rents mat\xe9riaux :\\n\\n- **Lasers \xe0 diode** : Excellents pour la gravure sur bois, le cuir et\\n  certains plastiques\\n- **Lasers CO2** : Parfaits pour d\xe9couper l\'acrylique, le bois et\\n  d\'autres mat\xe9riaux organiques\\n- **Lasers \xe0 fibre** : Id\xe9aux pour le marquage des m\xe9taux\\n\\nSi vous avez plusieurs types de lasers sur un syst\xe8me portique, la\\nprise en charge multi-laser de Rayforge vous permet d\'utiliser l\'outil\\noptimal pour chaque partie de votre projet.\\n\\n## Comment le configurer\\n\\n### 1. Configurer plusieurs lasers dans votre profil de machine\\n\\nAllez dans **Configuration de la machine \u2192 Lasers multiples** et\\nd\xe9finissez chaque module laser dans votre syst\xe8me. Vous pouvez sp\xe9cifier :\\n\\n- Le type de laser et la plage de puissance\\n- Les positions de d\xe9calage (si les lasers sont mont\xe9s \xe0 diff\xe9rents\\n  emplacements)\\n- La compatibilit\xe9 des mat\xe9riaux\\n\\nConsultez notre [Guide de configuration laser](/docs/machine/laser)\\npour des instructions d\xe9taill\xe9es.\\n\\n### 2. Assigner les lasers aux op\xe9rations\\n\\nLors de la cr\xe9ation d\'op\xe9rations dans votre projet :\\n\\n1. S\xe9lectionnez l\'op\xe9ration (Contour, Trame, etc.)\\n2. Dans les param\xe8tres de l\'op\xe9ration, choisissez le laser \xe0 utiliser\\n   dans le menu d\xe9roulant\\n3. Configurez les param\xe8tres de l\'op\xe9ration sp\xe9cifiques \xe0 ce laser\\n\\n### 3. Pr\xe9visualiser et ex\xe9cuter\\n\\nUtilisez l\'aper\xe7u 3D pour v\xe9rifier vos trajets d\'outil, puis envoyez la\\nt\xe2che \xe0 votre machine. Rayforge g\xe9n\xe9rera automatiquement les commandes\\nG-code appropri\xe9es pour basculer entre les lasers selon les besoins.\\n\\n## D\xe9tails techniques\\n\\nSous le capot, Rayforge utilise des commandes G-code pour basculer entre\\nles modules laser. L\'impl\xe9mentation exacte d\xe9pend de votre firmware et\\nde votre configuration mat\xe9rielle, mais les approches courantes incluent :\\n\\n- **M3/M4 avec d\xe9calages d\'outil** : Basculer entre les lasers en\\n  utilisant des commandes de changement d\'outil\\n- **Contr\xf4le GPIO** : Utiliser des broches GPIO prises en charge par le\\n  firmware pour activer/d\xe9sactiver diff\xe9rents modules laser\\n- **Macros personnalis\xe9es** : D\xe9finir des macros pr\xe9- et post-op\xe9ration\\n  pour la commutation laser\\n\\n## Pour commencer\\n\\nLa prise en charge multi-laser est disponible dans Rayforge 0.15 et\\nversions ult\xe9rieures. Pour d\xe9marrer :\\n\\n1. Mettez \xe0 jour vers la derni\xe8re version\\n2. Configurez votre profil de machine avec plusieurs lasers\\n3. Testez sur un projet exp\xe9rimental !\\n\\nConsultez la [documentation des profils de machine](/docs/machine/general)\\npour plus de d\xe9tails.\\n\\n---\\n\\n*Vous avez une configuration multi-laser ? Nous serions ravis d\'entendre\\nparler de votre exp\xe9rience ! Partagez vos projets et vos commentaires sur\\n[GitHub](https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge).*"},{"id":"welcome-to-rayforge","metadata":{"permalink":"/fr/blog/welcome-to-rayforge","source":"@site/i18n/fr/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2024-12-15-welcome-to-rayforge.md","title":"Bienvenue dans Rayforge : Logiciel de contr\xf4le laser moderne","description":"Fen\xeatre principale de Rayforge","date":"2024-12-15T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"introduction","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/introduction"},{"inline":true,"label":"fonctionnalit\xe9s","permalink":"/fr/blog/tags/fonctionnalites"}],"readingTime":2.13,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Rayforge Team","title":"Core development team","url":"https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge","imageURL":"/fr/images/icon.svg","key":"rayforge_team","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"welcome-to-rayforge","title":"Bienvenue dans Rayforge : Logiciel de contr\xf4le laser moderne","authors":"rayforge_team","tags":["introduction","fonctionnalit\xe9s"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Prise en charge multi-laser - Choisissez diff\xe9rents lasers pour chaque op\xe9ration","permalink":"/fr/blog/multi-laser-support"}},"content":"![Fen\xeatre principale de Rayforge](/screenshots/main-standard.png)\\n\\nNous sommes ravis de vous pr\xe9senter Rayforge, un \xe9metteur de G-code moderne\\net open-source, ainsi qu\'un logiciel de contr\xf4le con\xe7u sp\xe9cifiquement pour\\nles d\xe9coupeuses et graveuses laser bas\xe9es sur GRBL.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Pourquoi Rayforge ?\\n\\nDans le monde de la d\xe9coupe et de la gravure laser, disposer d\'un logiciel\\nfiable et intuitif est tout aussi important que d\'avoir du mat\xe9riel de\\nqualit\xe9. Rayforge a \xe9t\xe9 con\xe7u d\xe8s le d\xe9part en mettant l\'accent sur :\\n\\n- **Exp\xe9rience utilisateur moderne** : Construit avec Gtk4 et Libadwaita,\\n  Rayforge offre une interface claire et native qui se sent comme chez\\n  elle sur Linux et Windows\\n- **Fonctionnalit\xe9s professionnelles** : Flux de travail multi-couches,\\n  aper\xe7u 3D, int\xe9gration de cam\xe9ra et g\xe9n\xe9ration de trajets avanc\xe9e\\n- **Flexibilit\xe9** : Prise en charge de plusieurs profils de machine,\\n  macros personnalis\xe9es et options de configuration \xe9tendues\\n- **D\xe9veloppement ouvert** : Pilot\xe9 par la communaut\xe9, les contributions\\n  sont les bienvenues\\n\\n## Qu\'est-ce qui diff\xe9rencie Rayforge ?\\n\\n### Op\xe9rations multi-couches\\n\\nL\'une des caract\xe9ristiques remarquables de Rayforge est son flux de\\ntravail multi-couches. Assignez diff\xe9rentes op\xe9rations \xe0 diff\xe9rentes\\ncouches dans votre conception \u2014 gravez des d\xe9tails fins sur une couche,\\npuis d\xe9coupez la pi\xe8ce sur une autre. Le tout g\xe9r\xe9 de mani\xe8re fluide dans\\nune seule interface.\\n\\n### Aper\xe7u 3D du G-code\\n\\nAvant d\'envoyer votre t\xe2che \xe0 la machine, visualisez exactement ce qui\\nva se passer avec notre aper\xe7u 3D du G-code. D\xe9tectez les probl\xe8mes\\npotentiels avant qu\'ils ne surviennent et \xe9conomisez du temps et des\\nmat\xe9riaux.\\n\\n### Int\xe9gration de cam\xe9ra\\n\\nUtilisez une cam\xe9ra USB pour l\'alignement pr\xe9cis de la pi\xe8ce, le\\npositionnement, et m\xeame le tra\xe7age de l\'arri\xe8re-plan. Parfait pour\\npositionner des conceptions sur des mat\xe9riaux pr\xe9existants ou cr\xe9er\\ndes gabarits.\\n\\n### G\xe9n\xe9ration de trajets avanc\xe9e\\n\\nRayforge inclut un tra\xe7age d\'image de haute qualit\xe9, une optimisation\\ndu temps de d\xe9placement, un lissage des trajets et une interpolation\\nde la taille du spot pour garantir que vos projets se r\xe9alisent exactement\\ncomme pr\xe9vu.\\n\\n## Pour commencer\\n\\nPr\xeat \xe0 essayer Rayforge ? Consultez notre\\n[Guide d\'installation](/docs/getting-started/installation) pour d\xe9marrer.\\nQue vous utilisiez Ubuntu, une autre distribution Linux via Snap, ou\\nWindows, nous avons ce qu\'il vous faut.\\n\\n## Rejoignez la communaut\xe9\\n\\nRayforge est open-source et pilot\xe9 par la communaut\xe9. Nous accueillons\\nles contributions de toutes sortes :\\n\\n- Signalez des bugs et demandez des fonctionnalit\xe9s sur\\n  [GitHub Issues](https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge/issues)\\n- Contribuez au code via les\\n  [pull requests](https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge/pulls)\\n- Am\xe9liorez la documentation\\n- Partagez vos projets et exp\xe9riences\\n\\n---\\n\\n*Vous avez des questions ou des commentaires ? Rejoignez la conversation\\nsur GitHub ou consultez notre [documentation](/docs/getting-started/installation).*"}]}}')}}]);